						               													<description>A card game for 2-4+ players based on the Video Game: Zelda the Wind Walker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players share a common deck.  All cards are of 2 basic types: Quest Cards and Hero Cards. There are 7 types of hero cards:  Weapons, Items, Defence, Actions, Friends, Special, Tricks. There are 7 types of quest cards: Location, Treasure, Enemy, Boss, Monster, Obstacle, Objectives. Each card has a point value ranging from 1 to 10 and a special effect (e.g. search deck, bonus, draw card).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To start each player is dealt 5 cards to form their hand. Players then take it in turns with each turn comprising 5 phases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.   Destiny Phase&amp;#10;-     Draw 2 cards and place them in your hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2.    Adventure Phase&amp;#10;-     First, play 1 card to your own tableau (the area in front of a player) or discard 1 card. &amp;#10;-     Second, play 1 card to an opponent&amp;rsquo;s tableau or discard 1 card. &amp;#10;-     There are 14 types of cards. A tableau can contain a max of 14 cards - 1 of each type. A card may be placed so as to replace a card of the same type already in play in a tableau in which case the replaced card is discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3.    Option Phase&amp;#10;-     You may do one of the following 4 Options:&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Side Quest: Gain 1 Upgrade&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Mini Game: Draw 1 Card&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Picto Box: Gain 1 Quest Point&amp;#10;&amp;bull;    Missing Link: Gain 2 Exploration Points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4.    Quest Phase&amp;#10;-     You may complete a quest. To do this, you must have at least 5 hero cards of different types present in your tableau. You must also have at least 5 quest cards of different types present in your tableau.  Also, the total score of your hero cards must equal or exceed that of the quest cards. &amp;#10;-     Score Quest Points equal to the total value of the quest (nor hero) cards played &amp;#10;After a quest is scored, discard your tableau and take an extra turn immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5.    End Phase&amp;#10;-     Max hand size is 5 cards. Discard extras.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to acquire 100+ Quest Points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
